        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 1:59PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Malta, or near DeKalb, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
DeKalb, Cortland, Maple Park, Malta, Sycamore, and Virgil.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
